==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: permanent-press
<hw>permanent-press</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A fabric that has been
chemically processed to resist wrinkles and hold its shape.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> permanent press, permanent-press fabric, durable
press, durable-press fabric.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>permanent-press</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: permanent-press
<hw>permanent-press</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Having a permanent crease,
or remaining unwrinkled without pressing; -- used of fabrics that do not
require ironing.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> drip-dry.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>permanent wave</ent>⟦br⟧
